    "what_description": "Verbena peruviana is a species of flowering plant in the family Verbenaceae, native to South America. It is an evergreen shrub, growing up to 1-2 meters in height, with a woody base and slender branches. The leaves are opposite, elliptical in shape, and 2-4 cm long, with a leathery texture and serrated margins. The flowers are small, white or purple, and borne in axillary clusters, producing a sweet fragrance. The plant is often grown for its ornamental value, and is used in herbal medicine for its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties.",
