    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Verbena peruviana are antimicrobial, which is attributed to the presence of volatile oils that inhibit the growth of microorganisms. These bioactive compounds also exhibit antioxidant properties, scavenging free radicals and protecting cells from oxidative damage. Additionally, the anti-inflammatory effects of Verbena peruviana are associated with the presence of flavonoids and saponins, which modulate the inflammatory response and reduce swelling. The antispasmodic activity of this plant is due to the presence of iridoids and phenolic acids, which relax smooth muscle and alleviate spasms. Furthermore, the analgesic properties of Verbena peruviana are thought to be mediated by the bioactive compounds, which interact with pain receptors and reduce nociception, providing relief from pain.",
